A transaction intended to update Colleague with externally modified data can in , turn trigger Colleague to generate a transaction to update external , applications. To mitigate this 'mirror-image' effect, the AMQP message broker , maintains an internal record of each transaction inbound to Colleague as a , means of identifying (and suppressing) a resulting 'mirror-image' outbound , transaction. If you do not want a single value selected to be assumed, to be what you want, a value of Yes for this field will, force a call to the resolution screen even if only 1 hit., Typing an actual key instead of a LookUp ... specification, will be considered equivalent to 1 hit and will resolve.
